701134f-b.title: Bronx: Grand Concourse - 150th Street (East)
701134f-b.text:
Grand Concourse, south from E. 151st Street. Note,
at E. 150th Street, the skeleton of a new United States
Post Office.
View 2 is south from E. 150th Street and shows the
post office site extending to E. 149th Street.
July 7, 1936
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr

701133f-b.title: Bronx: Grand Concourse - 150th Street (East)
701133f-b.text:
Grand Concourse, at the N. W. corner of E. 150th
Street, showing the Mott Avenue Methodist Episcopal
Church. This part of the Concourse was formerly Mott
Avenue.
May 16, 1928
P. L. Sperr
(2)
The same site, after the church was torn down.
June, 1940
P. L. Sperr
